@Prev "NODE_CHFIFTEEN"
@Toc "Main"

Chapter 16
**********

16.2 ioctl function
===================

   Instead of `ioctl' the function `IoctlSocket' has to be used.

16.3 Socket Operations
======================

   `sockatmark' is not supported by the standard AmigaOS BSD-socket
API, but by the Miami API.

16.8 ARP Cache Operations
=========================

   Miami's ARP cache is integrated with routing tables and accessible
through AF_ROUTE sockets, not through the obsolete SIOCxARP operations.


@EndNode

@Node "NODE_CHSEVENTEEN" "TCPIP.guide/NODE_CHSEVENTEEN"
@Next "NODE_CHEIGHTEEN"
@Prev "NODE_CHSIXTEEN"
@Toc "Main"

Chapter 17. Routing Sockets
***************************

   Routing sockets are only supported by Miami, not by older protocol
stacks.

17.4 sysctl Operations
======================

   The `sysctl' function is not supported by the standard AmigaOS
BSD-socket API, but the Miami API has the equivalent function
`MiamiSysCtl'. The objects MiamiSysCtl operates on (and the resulting
tree structure) are slightly different from the one described in the
text. Please see the C header files for lists of all supported objects.

17.6 Interface Name and Index Functions
=======================================

   The functions defined in this section are not supported by the
standard AmigaOS BSD-socket API, but by the Miami API.


@EndNode

@Node "NODE_CHEIGHTEEN" "TCPIP.guide/NODE_CHEIGHTEEN"
@Next "NODE_CHNINETEEN"
@Prev "NODE_CHSEVENTEEN"
@Toc "Main"

Chapter 18. Broadcasting
************************

18.2 Broadcast Addresses
========================

   Commenting on the indented text: Miami converts 255.255.255.255 to
the subnet-directed broadcast address of the outgoing interface.  In
the case of a multi-homed hosts (which will only be an issue with Miami
Deluxe) broadcasts are sent to the primary interface.

18.5 Race Condition
===================

   The problem described in this section is specific to Unix signal
handling only, and of no concern for AmigaOS programmers.


@EndNode

@Node "NODE_CHNINETEEN" "TCPIP.guide/NODE_CHNINETEEN"
@Next "NODE_CHTWENTY"
@Prev "NODE_CHEIGHTEEN"
@Toc "Main"

Chapter 19. Multicasting
************************

   Multicasting is only supported by the registered version of Miami,
not by older protocol stacks.


